text: No individual service or system running on the wired/wireless network should use more than 10 gigabytes of per day, regardless of whether it is inbound or outbound over the commodity network link
You may not run FTP, telnet, peer-to-peer, HTTP, IRC, DNS and mail servers on ResNet or UIC wireless-connected devices
Guests' network is rate-limited to 5 Mb/s per user
Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
The system will trigger an overuse notification if the  average for either inbound or outbound usage exceeds 10 GB per week
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall
